{"title_page": "Yp\u00e4j\u00e4", "text_new": "{{Infobox Finnish Municipality\n|name                   = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4\n|official_name          = {{lang|fi|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4n kunta}}<br />{{lang|sv|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 kommun}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality <!-- City, Town or Municipality-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = Ypaja church.jpg\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 Church\n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4.vaakuna.svg\n|shield_size            = \n|image_blank_emblem     = \n|blank_emblem_type      = \n|blank_emblem_size      = \n|image_map              = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 in [[Finland]]\n|image_dot_map          = \n|dot_mapsize            = \n|dot_map_caption        = \n|dot_x =  |dot_y = \n|pushpin_map            = <!-- name of a location map as per Template:Location_map -->\n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|province               = [[Southern Finland]]\n|region                 = [[Tavastia Proper]]\n|subregion              = Forssa sub-region\n<!-- Smaller parts (e.g. boroughs of a city) and seat of government -->\n|seat_type              = \n|seat                   = \n|parts_type             = \n|parts_style            = <!-- =list (for list), coll (for collapsed list), para (for paragraph format)\n                               Default is list if up to 5 items, coll if more than 5-->\n|parts                  = <!-- parts text, or header for parts list -->\n|p1                     = \n|p2                     = <!-- etc. up to p10: for separate parts to be listed-->\n|government_footnotes   = \n|leader_title           = Municipal manager\n|leader_name            = Sinikka Malin\n|leader_title1          = \n|leader_name1           = \n|leader_title2          = \n|leader_name2           = \n|leader_title3          = \n|leader_name3           = \n|established_title      = [[Charter]]\n|established_date       = 1876\n|established_title2     = \n|established_date2      = \n|established_title3     = \n|established_date3      = \n|extinct_title          = \n|extinct_date           = \n|area_urban_km2         = \n|area_metro_km2         = \n|population_metro       = \n|population_blank1_title  = \n|population_blank1        = \n|population_density_metro_km2 = \n|population_urban       = \n|population_density_urban_km2 = \n|population_note        = \n|finnish_official       = 1\n|swedish_official       = \n|sami_official          = \n|urbanisation           = \n|unemployment           = \n|blank1_name            = [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|Climate]]\n|blank1_info            = [[Subarctic climate|Dfc]]\n|blank2_name            = \n|blank2_info            = \n|blank3_name            = \n|blank3_info            = \n|blank4_name            = \n|blank4_info            = \n|coordinates_type       = \n<!-- latNS=N and longEW=E set by default -->\n|coordinates            = {{coord|60|48.5|N|023|17|E|display=inline,title}}\n|elevation_m            = \n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              = \n|website                = [http://www.ypaja.fi/ www.ypaja.fi]\n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Yp\u00e4j\u00e4''' is a [[municipalities of Finland|municipality]] located in the countryside of South-Western [[Finland]]. It belongs to the [[provinces of Finland|province]] of [[Southern Finland]] and the [[regions of Finland|region]] of [[Tavastia Proper]]. The municipality has a population of {{Formatnum:\n{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4}}}}\n({{#time: j F Y|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population count|sourcedate}}\n}})<ref name=\"population_count\" /> and covers an area of {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/total area|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4}}|km2}} of\nwhich {{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/waters area|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4}}|km2|abbr=on}}\nis water.<ref name=\"total_area\" /> The [[population density]] is\n{{convert|{{Infobox Finnish Municipality/population density|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4|round=2}}|PD/km2}}. The municipality is unilingually [[Finnish language|Finnish]].\n\nThe main population centre of Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 is a small village situated on the river [[Loimijoki]], between the towns of [[Forssa]] (23&nbsp;km to the east from Yp\u00e4j\u00e4) and [[Loimaa]] (15&nbsp;km to the west). Although officially part of the Forssa region, Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 is often also considered to belong to the Loimaa region as it has traditionally been influenced by both towns. Besides Loimaa, its direct neighbours are [[Jokioinen]], [[Humppila]], [[Somero]] and [[Koski Tl]].\n\nThe distances from Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 to the three major cities in southern Finland are relatively short: {{convert|74|km}} to [[Turku]], {{convert|96|km|abbr=on}} to [[Tampere]], and {{convert|132|km|abbr=on}} to the capital [[Helsinki]].\n\nYp\u00e4j\u00e4 is probably best known for [[horse]]s; the municipality e.g. has an Equine College and hosts an annual international [[equestrianism|riding competition]] called [[Finnderby]].\n\nYp\u00e4j\u00e4's coat of arms is designed by [[Aukusti Tuhka]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category-inline|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4}}\n*[http://www.ypaja.fi/ Municipality of Yp\u00e4j\u00e4] \u2013 Official website {{in lang|fi}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110720095015/http://www.hevosopisto.fi/index.phtml?page_id=3001&navi_id=3001&en=1%2F Equine College Yp\u00e4j\u00e4]\n\n{{TavastiaProper}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ypaja}}\n[[Category:Municipalities of Tavastia Proper]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1876]]\n\n\n{{SouthernFinland-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Finnish Municipality\n|name                   = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4\n|official_name          = {{lang|fi|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4n kunta}}<br />{{lang|sv|Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 kommun}}\n|other_name             = \n|native_name            = \n|native_name_lang       = \n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        = Municipality <!-- City, Town or Municipality-->\n|total_type             = <!-- to set a non-standard label for total area and population rows -->\n|motto                  = \n|image_skyline          = Ypaja church.jpg\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 Church\n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              = \n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              = \n|image_shield           = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4.vaakuna.svg\n|shield_size            = \n|image_blank_emblem     = \n|blank_emblem_type      = \n|blank_emblem_size      = \n|image_map              = Yp\u00e4j\u00e4.sijainti.suomi.2008.svg\n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = Location of Yp\u00e4j\u00e4 in [[Finland]]\n|image_dot_map          = \n|dot_mapsize            = \n|dot_map_caption        = \n|dot_x =  |dot_y = \n|pushpin_map            = <!-- name of a location map as per Template:Location_map -->\n|pushpin_label_position = <!-- position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption    = \n|pushpin_mapsize        = \n|province               = [[Southern Finland]]\n|region                 = [[Tavastia Proper]]\n|subregion              = Forssa sub-region\n<!-- Smaller parts (e.g. boroughs of a city) and seat of government -->\n|seat_type              = \n|seat                   = \n|parts_type             = \n|parts_style            = <!-- =list (for list), coll (for collapsed list), para (for paragraph format)\n                 