rst1=Robert Bruce\n|authorlink1=Robert Bruce Ware\n|last2=Kisriev\n|first2=Enver\n|authorlink2=Enver Kisriev\n|year=2009\n|title=Dagestan: Russian Hegemony and Islamic Resistance in the North Caucasus\n|publisher=Routledge\n|isbn=978-0765620286\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| last1       = Akhmadov\n| first1      = Ilyas\n| authorlink1 = Ilyas Akhmadov\n| last2       = Lanskoy\n| first2      = Miriam\n| authorlink2 = Miriam Lanskoy\n| last3       = Brzezinski\n| first3      = Zbigniew\n| authorlink3 = Zbigniew Brzezinski\n| title       = The Chechen Struggle: Independence Won and Lost\n| year        = 2010\n| publisher   = Palgrave Macmillan\n| isbn        = 978-0-230-10534-8\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| last1       = Soldatov\n| first1      = Andrei\n| authorlink1 = Andrei Soldatov\n| last2       = Borogan\n| first2      = Irina\n| authorlink2 = Irina Borogan\n| title       = The New Nobility: The Restoration of Russia's Security State and the Enduring Legacy of the KGB\n| year        = 2010\n| publisher   = PublicAffairs\n| isbn        = 978-1-58648-802-4\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| first      = John\n| last       = Dunlop\n| authorlink = John B. Dunlop\n| title      = The Moscow Bombings of September 1999: Examinations of Russian Terrorist Attacks at the Onset of Vladimir Putin's Rule\n| publisher  = Stuttgart: Ibidem\n| year       = 2012\n| isbn       = 978-3-8382-0388-1\n}}\n\n* {{Citation\n| first      = Brian Glyn\n| last       = WilliamsA\n| authorlink = Brian Glyn Williams\n| title      = Inferno in Chechnya: The Russian-Chechen Wars, the Al Qaeda Myth, and the Boston Marathon Bombings\n| publisher  = ForeEdge\n| year       = 2015\n| isbn       = 978-1-61168-737-8\n}}\n\n{{Chechen wars}}\n[[Category:Explosions in 1999]]\n[[Category:Russian apartment bombings| ]]\n[[Category:Censorship in Russia]]\n[[Category:Deep politics]]\n[[Category:Vladimir Putin]]\n[[Category:Building collapses in Russia]]\n[[Category:Chechen\u2013Russian conflict]]\n[[Category:Events in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents in Russia in 1999]]\n[[Category:Improvised explosive device bombings in Russia]]\n[[Category:Mass murder in 1999]]\n[[Category:20th-century mass murder in Russia]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1999]]\n[[Category:Massacres in Russia]]\n[[Category:1999 crimes in Russia]]\n[[Category:Murder in Moscow]]\n[[Category:Federal Security Service of the Russian Federation]]\n[[Category:Second Chechen War]]\n[[Category:Terrorist incidents in Moscow]]\n[[Category:1990s in Moscow]]\n[[Category:September 1999 events in Europe]]\n", "name_user": "Document hippo", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eRyazan incident:style", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Russian_apartment_bombings"}
{"title_page": "Bluetech Award", "text_new": "{{short description|Annual award presented by the Clean Air Alliance of China}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|date=June 2016}}\n{{more citations needed|date=June 2016}}\n{{Underlinked|date=June 2016}}\n{{Orphan|date=September 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox award\n| name = Bluetech International Clean Air Technology Award\n| image = \n| image_size = <!-- or | image_upright = -->\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| description = \n| sponsor = Clean Air Alliance of China\n| date = <!-- {{start date|2015|12|12}} -->\n| location = <!-- or | venue = or | site = -->\n| country = China\n| presenter = \n| host = <!-- or | hosts = -->\n| former name = \n| website = <!-- {{URL|en.bluetechaward.com}} -->\n}}\nThe '''Bluetech International Clean Air Technology Award''' (also called '''Bluetech Award'''), is an annual award presented by the Clean Air Alliance of China (CAAC) to recognize outstanding technologies that prevent and control different forms and sources of [[air pollution]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.cleanairchina.org/cus/en08/index.html|title=Bluetech|website=www.cleanairchina.org|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>. The award examines each [[technology]] for breakthrough potential in terms of technological performance,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.environmentalleader.com/2015/09/clean-air-tech-competition-seeks-pollution-treatment-providers/|title=Clean Air Tech Competition Seeks Pollution Treatment Providers|last=Hardcastle|first=Jessica Lyons|date=2015-09-04|website=Environmental Leader|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> [[environmental impact]], and financial feasibility with CAAC's standardized technology assessment methodology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.cleanairchina.org/channel/type/70-3079-1.html?menuId=0|title=Products - Bluetech Clean Air Alliance|website=en.cleanairchina.org|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> The award selection committee consists of technical professionals, industrial experts and testing specialists that are chosen every year to fit each year's award categories. Technologies from around the world are eligible to apply.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebeijinger.com/blog/2015/08/27/bluetech-award-competition-clean-air-companies-join-fight-against-air-pollution|title=Clean Air Tech Competition Aims to Accelerate Fight Against Air Pollution in China|last=schreursm|date=2015-08-27|website=www.thebeijinger.com|language=EN|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>\n\nThe award ceremony, called the Bluetech International Clean Air Forum, features research leaders, industries, investors and policymakers in [[China]] and abroad to address global industry and policy trends in the [[Air pollution|air quality]] sector<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cameraitacina.com/en/events/bluetech-award|title=Bluetech Award {{!}} China-Italy Chamber of Commerce|website=www.cameraitacina.com|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>. Private follow-up events, held in [[Beijing]] and other pilot regions, are organised for Alliance members and selected technology companies.\nThe first Bluetech Award Ceremony was held on December 12, 2015, in [[Beijing|Beijing, China]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebeijinger.com/blog/2016/01/19/clean-air-accolades-mayair-wins-bluetech-award|title=Clean-Air Accolades: MayAir Wins the Bluetech Award|last=Jerry|date=2016-01-19|website=www.thebeijinger.com|language=EN|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> The second Bluetech Award Ceremony is planned for December 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cameraitacina.com/en/news/bluetech-award-calling-all-air-pollution-technologies|title=Bluetech Award: Calling all air pollution technologies! {{!}} China-Italy Chamber of Commerce|website=www.cameraitacina.com|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>.\n\n==Winners==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award year !! Technology Name !! Applicant  !! Category\n|-\n| 2015 ||[[Diesel particulate filter|Diesel Particulate Filter System]]|| Wuxi WeifuLida Catalytic Converter Co., Ltd. ||[[Diesel engine]] emission reduction technologies & clean energy substitutes\n|-\n| 2015 || Multi Functional Diesel Performance Additive || Total Petroleum ([[Shanghai]]) Co., Ltd. || Diesel engine emission reduction technologies & clean energy substitutes\n|-\n| 2015 || Low Emission Control Technology for Valves || Garlock Sealing Technologies (Shanghai) Co., Ltd. ||[[Volatile organic compound|VOC]]<nowiki/>s substitution, monitoring and pollution prevention\n|-\n| 2015 || MayAir \"Electric-Pocket\" Technology || MayAir Technology (China) Co., Ltd || Indoor [[Air quality|air quality monitoring]] and [[Air purifier|air purification]]\n|-\n| 2015 || EKEAIR MKJ4000 Air Purification Disinfector || Jiaxing Sanyin Environmental Purification Technology Co., Ltd. || Indoor air quality monitoring and air purification\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/garlock-receives-prestigious-award-for-advances-in-emissions-control-technology-2089493.htm\n* {{cite journal |doi=10.1016/S1350-4789(16)30054-X |title=Clean Air Alliance of China presents award to Garlock |journal=Sealing Technology |volume=2016 |issue=3 |pages=6 |year=2016 }}\n* http://announce.ft.com/Detail/?DocKey=1323-12627860-1H6SQN9RL5P0D7O1CBKIGI8OR8)\n* http://www.cameraitacina.com/en/news/2nd-bluetech-international-air-technology-award\n\n==External links==\n* [http://en.bluetechaward.com/ Official website]\n* [http://en.cleanairchina.org CAAC website]\n\n[[Category:Environmentalism]]\n[[Category:Pollution in China]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Annual award presented by the Clean Air Alliance of China}}\n{{Multiple issues|\n{{notability|date=June 2016}}\n{{more citations needed|date=June 2016}}\n{{Underlinked|date=June 2016}}\n{{Orphan|date=September 2018}}\n}}\n\n{{Infobox award\n| name = Bluetech International Clean Air Technology Award\n| image = \n| image_size = <!-- or | image_upright = -->\n| alt = \n| caption = \n| description = \n| sponsor = Clean Air Alliance of China\n| date = <!-- {{start date|2015|12|12}} -->\n| location = <!-- or | venue = or | site = -->\n| country = China\n| presenter = \n| host = <!-- or | hosts = -->\n| former name = \n| website = <!-- {{URL|en.bluetechaward.com}} -->\n}}\nThe '''Bluetech International Clean Air Technology Award''' (also called '''Bluetech Award'''), is an annual award presented by the Clean Air Alliance of China (CAAC) to recognise outstanding technologies that prevent and control different forms and sources of [[air pollution]]. The award examines each technology for breakthrough potential in terms of technological performance,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.environmentalleader.com/2015/09/clean-air-tech-competition-seeks-pollution-treatment-providers/|title=Clean Air Tech Competition Seeks Pollution Treatment Providers|last=Hardcastle|first=Jessica Lyons|date=2015-09-04|website=Environmental Leader|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> environmental impact, and financial feasibility with CAAC's standardised technology assessment methodology.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://en.cleanairchina.org/channel/type/70-3079-1.html?menuId=0|title=Products - Bluetech Clean Air Alliance|website=en.cleanairchina.org|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> The award selection committee consists of technical professionals, industrial experts and testing specialists that are chosen every year to fit each year's award categories. Technologies from around the world are eligible to apply.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebeijinger.com/blog/2015/08/27/bluetech-award-competition-clean-air-companies-join-fight-against-air-pollution|title=Clean Air Tech Competition Aims to Accelerate Fight Against Air Pollution in China|last=schreursm|date=2015-08-27|website=www.thebeijinger.com|language=EN|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>\n\nThe award ceremony, called the Bluetech International Clean Air Forum, features research leaders, industries, investors and policymakers in [[China]] and abroad to address global industry and policy trends in the air quality sector<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cameraitacina.com/en/events/bluetech-award|title=Bluetech Award {{!}} China-Italy Chamber of Commerce|website=www.cameraitacina.com|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>. Private follow-up events, held in [[Beijing]] and other pilot regions, are organised for Alliance members and selected technology companies.\nThe first Bluetech Award Ceremony was held on December 12, 2015, in [[Beijing|Beijing, China]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thebeijinger.com/blog/2016/01/19/clean-air-accolades-mayair-wins-bluetech-award|title=Clean-Air Accolades: MayAir Wins the Bluetech Award|last=Jerry|date=2016-01-19|website=www.thebeijinger.com|language=EN|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref> The second Bluetech Award Ceremony is planned for December 2016<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cameraitacina.com/en/news/bluetech-award-calling-all-air-pollution-technologies|title=Bluetech Award: Calling all air pollution technologies! {{!}} China-Italy Chamber of Commerce|website=www.cameraitacina.com|access-date=2019-09-10}}</ref>.\n\n==Winners==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Award year !! Technology Name !! Applicant  !! Category\n|-\n| 2015 || Diesel Particulate Filter System || Wuxi WeifuLida Catalytic Converter Co., Ltd. ||[[Diesel engine]] emission reduction technologies & clean energy substitutes\n|-\n| 2015 || Multi Functional Diesel Performance Additive || Total Petroleum ([[Shanghai]]) Co., Ltd. || Diesel engine emission reduction technologies & clean energy substitutes\n|-\n| 2015 || Low Emission Control Technology for Valves || Garlock Sealing Technologies (Shanghai) Co., Ltd. ||[[Volatile organic compound|VOC]]<nowiki/>s substitution, monitoring and pollution prevention\n|-\n| 2015 || MayAir \"Electric-Pocket\" Technology || MayAir Technology (China) Co., Ltd || Indoor air quality monitoring and [[Air purifier|air purification]]\n|-\n| 2015 || EKEAIR MKJ4000 Air Purification Disinfector || Jiaxing Sanyin Environmental Purification Technology Co., Ltd. || Indoor air quality monitoring and air purification\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n* http://www.marketwired.com/press-release/garlock-receives-prestigious-award-for-advances-in-emissions-control-technology-2089493.htm\n* {{cite journal |doi=10.1016/S1350-4789(16)30054-X |title=Clean Air Alliance of China presents award to Garlock |journal=Sealing Technology |volume=2016 |issue=3 |pages=6 |year=2016 }}\n* http://announce.ft.com/Detail/?DocKey=1323-12627860-1H6SQN9RL5P0D7O1CBKIGI8OR8)\n* http://www.cameraitacina.com/en/news/2nd-bluetech-international-air-technology-award\n\n==External links==\n* [http://en.bluetechaward.com/ Official website]\n* [http://en.cleanairchina.org CAAC website]\n\n[[Category:Environmentalism]]\n[[Category:Pollution in China]]\n", "name_user": "Inkmesh", "label": "safe", "comment": "I have added few in-article links to existing Wikipedia pages.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bluetech_Award"}
